    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document specifies IS-IS autoconfiguration mechanisms.  The key components are IS-IS System ID self-generation, duplication detection, and duplication resolution.  These mechanisms provide limited IS-IS functions and are therefore suitable for networks where plug-and-play configuration is expected.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
